My dad laughed out loud.
I turned away and hid my anger.
Afterwards he was silent.
Nobody said a word.
I felt bothered by him.
From that time I could not trust his words.

When I was a child, I had questions about electricity, how things worked.
I wanted to know differences between creatures. Or facts of history regarding many wars.
Nowadays we have different opinions about issues people are discussing entire life. When we watch a movie, television program, read magazines there are quite many issues on which we are not sure what obtainable information is right.
Conversation among us is very important for every age. Talking with our close, personal people gives us trust.
Reading articles in magazine news or social media regarding wrong or right cases we must hold seriousness within us.
 Photography insight, climate change, researching self esteem, gender inequality or LGBTQIA people are one of many social, science, cultural problems. We observe many situations in levels of life and read about people issues, topics on which we have to focus.
My father needs information. He looks for previews about new books or other publications.
He cannot go to stores any day the same.
That’s why he has a lot of information online.
That is my general point these days.
I want to write my book about many topics related to life.
One of them is… Our insecurities and trust about our surroundings.
I make things easier for myself reading about things regarding people discussion, culture, gender, climate change
